'''監票員'''是指為防止出現[[選舉|選舉]]舞弊而在選舉中負責監督選舉過程以及計票過程的人<ref name="Maryland">{{Cite web|title=Challengers and Watchers|url=http://www.elections.state.md.us/get_involved/challenger_watcher.html|accessdate=30 March 2015|work=Maryland State Board of Elections|publisher=Maryland State Board of Elections|archive-date=2018-01-13|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180113092208/http://www.elections.state.md.us/get_involved/challenger_watcher.html|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name="Chicago">{{Cite web|title=All About Poll Watchers: Rights & Responsibilities|url=http://www.chicagoelections.com/en/serving-as-a-poll-watcher.html|accessdate=30 March 2015|work=Chicago Board of Election Commissioners|publisher=Chicago Board of Election Commissioners|archive-date=2020-10-21|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201021142033/https://chicagoelections.com/en/serving-as-a-poll-watcher.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>。每個政黨均可向每個投票站派出監票員。這些監票員通常須避免與選民直接接觸、避免穿戴含有政治口號的服飾以及禁止在選舉期間對選舉施加影響。监督员还可以向其所在的政黨竞选总部匯報非官方结果，因为正式结果可能需要一段时间後才能发布。

